  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Noninvasive brain stimulations (NIBS) will be used in chronic stroke patients to improve
      motor learning.

      Functional magnetic resonance imaging will be used to evaluate the mechanisms underlying
      motor learning in healthy volunteers and in chronic stroke patients.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      transcranial direct current stimulation will be used for NIBS
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
